claim.claim-text:
A system for correcting or reducing a conicity or a mass distribution imbalance of a tread strip (132), the system comprising:
an extruder (10) for extruding a tread strip (132) through at least one profile die (46), the tread strip (132) having a right hand side and a left hand side;
a left profile die for extruding a chimney (32, 304, 312) on a left hand side of the tread strip (132);
a right profile die for extruding a chimney (32, 304, 312) on a right hand side of the tread strip (132);
a chimney extrusion means in fluid communication with the left and/or the right profile die;
means for measuring or calculating the mass or the thickness of the left hand side of the tread strip (132) and of the right hand side of the tread strip (132);
means for comparing the left hand side measured or calculated mass or thickness with a predetermined left hand side mass or thickness;
means for comparing the right hand side measured or calculated mass or thickness with a predetermined right hand side mass or thickness; and
means for extruding the chimney (32, 304, 312) through the right profile die if the right hand side measured or calculated mass or thickness exceeds the predetermined right hand side mass or thickness, and means for extruding the chimney (32, 304, 312) through the left profile die if the left right hand side measured or calculated mass or thickness exceeds the predetermined left hand side mass or thickness.
